This is the core specification for Pantheon: a multi-basis reasoning and execution engine.
High-Level Overview
Pantheon is designed as a unified “thinking” kernel that processes any input (state, problem, experience) through multiple interpretive lenses (domains/bases) simultaneously, selects the minimal sufficient set, synthesizes actions, and stores memory in a structured, reversible way.
It’s not a narrow LLM wrapper — it’s an architecture meant to enforce comprehensive, grounded reasoning by forcing the system to ask “every important question” before acting. Think of it as a meta-reasoning engine that routes problems across semantic, mathematical, scientific, strategic, ethical, mythic, and other domains to avoid blind spots.
Core Idea (from the doc):
Reality is interpreted through multiple constraint systems. Power = selecting the right ones at the right time.
Languages choose how you SEE. Mathematics chooses how things CAN CHANGE. Science constrains what IS POSSIBLE.
It integrates ~22 domains (listed in the tensor) and aims to power things like PantheonOS (an operating system?) and Inner Atlas (real-time embodied/self-state tracking).
Key Components
	1	Canonical Tensor Represents any state as a multi-dimensional object across all domains (semantic, structural/math, empirical/science, biological, economic, psychological, strategic, memetic, mythic, cybernetic, etc.).
	2	Execution Pipeline
	◦	Semantic Encoding → Structural Modeling → Constraint Filtering → Domain Routing (Conductor) → Multi-Domain Interpretation → Action Synthesis → Confidence Scoring → Memory Compression (EchoFrame).
	3	Domain Routing (Conductor Daemon) Intelligently picks only the minimum sufficient domains based on triggers (e.g., stress → Psychological + Cybernetic + Economic). Avoids overfitting/noise.
	4	Interpretation & Action Synthesis Each domain outputs a structured reading ({domain, summary, signal, evidence}). Actions emerge from overlaps and are ranked by confidence.
	5	Daemons (background processes):
	◦	Conductor: Domain routing.
	◦	Spider: Builds graphs/relations.
	◦	Hound: Detects anomalies/patterns.
	◦	Mirror (Solomon): Ethical/invariant gate (requires ≥0.7 cross-domain confidence).
	◦	EchoFrame: Compresses experiences into layered memory (raw → delta → doctrine) for the Mother Duck Ledger.
	6	Memory & Compression Append-only, reversible. Promotes stable patterns to “doctrines.” Ties directly into your earlier Wallflower idea — provenance, traceability, anti-drift.
	7	Guardrails Strong emphasis on separating Signal (raw data) vs. Interpretation vs. Narrative, no domain overriding reality, reversible compression, no irreversible autonomous actions.
